name: Phyrexian Negator
text: Trample\nWhenever Phyrexian Negator is dealt damage, sacrifice that many permanents.
flavor: They exist to cease.

name: Carrion Feeder
text: Carrion Feeder can't block.\nSacrifice a creature: Put a +1/+1 counter on Carrion Feeder.
flavor: Stinking of rot, it leaps between gravestones in search of its next meal.

name: Phyrexian Battleflies
text: Flying\n{B}: Phyrexian Battleflies gets +1/+0 until end of turn. Activate this ability no more than twice each turn.
flavor: After encountering them, Squee finally lost his appetite for bugs.

name: Phyrexian Denouncer
text: {T}, Sacrifice Phyrexian Denouncer: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: "The first stage of the illness: rash and nausea."\n—Phyrexian progress notes

name: Bone Shredder
text: Flying\nEcho {2}{B} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\nWhen Bone Shredder enters the battlefield, destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature.

name: Phyrexian Ghoul
text: Sacrifice a creature: Phyrexian Ghoul gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: Phyrexia wastes nothing. Its food chain is a spiraling cycle.

name: Priest of Gix
text: When Priest of Gix enters the battlefield, add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: "Gix doesn't want a people to rule but puppets to entertain his madness."\n—Xantcha, Phyrexian outcast

name: Phyrexian Broodlings
text: {1}, Sacrifice a creature: Put a +1/+1 counter on Phyrexian Broodlings.
flavor: With limited resources and near unlimited time, Kerrick used parts from one beast to build another.

name: Sanguine Guard
text: First strike\n{1}{B}: Regenerate Sanguine Guard.
flavor: "Father of Machines! Your filigree gaze carves us, and the scars dance upon our grateful flesh."\n—Phyrexian Scriptures

name: Phyrexian Debaser
text: Flying\n{T}, Sacrifice Phyrexian Debaser: Target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor: "The second stage of the illness: high fever and severe infectiousness."\n—Phyrexian progress notes

name: Order of Yawgmoth
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\nWhenever Order of Yawgmoth deals damage to a player, that player discards a card.

name: Phyrexian Defiler
text: {T}, Sacrifice Phyrexian Defiler: Target creature gets -3/-3 until end of turn.
flavor: "The third stage of the illness: muscle aches and persistent cough."\n—Phyrexian progress notes

name: Phyrexian Plaguelord
text: {T}, Sacrifice Phyrexian Plaguelord: Target creature gets -4/-4 until end of turn.\nSacrifice a creature: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: "The final stage of the illness: delirium, convulsions, and death."\n—Phyrexian progress notes

name: Phyrexian Hulk
flavor:
It doesn't think. It doesn't feel.
It doesn't laugh or cry.
All it does from dusk till dawn
Is make the soldiers die.
—Onean children's rhyme

name: Phyrexian Gargantua
text: When Phyrexian Gargantua enters the battlefield, you draw two cards and you lose 2 life.
flavor: Other Phyrexians have nightmares about the gargantua.

name: Phyrexian Colossus
text: Phyrexian Colossus doesn't untap during your untap step.\nPay 8 life: Untap Phyrexian Colossus.\nPhyrexian Colossus can't be blocked except by three or more creatures.

name: Voltaic Key
text: {1}, {T}: Untap target artifact.
flavor: The key did not work on a single lock, yet it opened many doors.

name: Dark Ritual
text: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: "From void evolved Phyrexia. Great Yawgmoth, Father of Machines, saw its perfection. Thus the Grand Evolution began."\n—Phyrexian Scriptures

name: Lightning Greaves
text: Equipped creature has haste and shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)\nEquip {0}
flavor: After lightning struck the cliffs, the ore became iron, the iron became steel, and the steel became greaves. The lightning never left.

name: Phyrexian Totem
text: {T}: Add {B} to your mana pool.\n{2}{B}: Phyrexian Totem becomes a 5/5 black Horror artifact creature with trample until end of turn.\nWhenever Phyrexian Totem is dealt damage, if it's a creature, sacrifice that many permanents.

name: Phyrexian Vault
text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice a creature: Draw a card.
flavor: "The secrets of Phyrexia are expensive. You will pay in brass and bone, steel and sinew."\n—Kaervek

name: Puppet Strings
text: {2}, {T}: You may tap or untap target creature.
flavor: "Have no illusions," Volrath warned Greven, "about free will."

name: Whispersilk Cloak
text: Equipped creature can't be blocked and has shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)\nEquip {2}
flavor: Such cloaks are in high demand both by assassins and by those who fear them.

name: Worn Powerstone
text: Worn Powerstone enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {C}{C} to your mana pool.
flavor: Even a fragment of a powerstone contains within it not just energy, but space—vast dimensions trapped in fragile crystal.

name: Slay
text: Destroy target green creature. It can't be regenerated.\nDraw a card.
flavor: The elves had the edge in guile, skill, and valor. But in the end, only sheer numbers mattered.

name: Hideous End
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. Its controller loses 2 life.
flavor: Death is a generous author, always willing to grant a stirring final chapter.

name: Phyrexian Arena
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor: An audience of one with the malice of thousands.

name: Hornet Cannon
text: {3}, {T}: Put a 1/1 colorless Insect artifact creature token with flying and haste named Hornet onto the battlefield. Destroy it at the beginning of the next end step.

name: Phyrexian Processor
text: As Phyrexian Processor enters the battlefield, pay any amount of life.\n{4}, {T}: Put an X/X black Minion creature token onto the battlefield, where X is the life paid as Phyrexian Processor entered the battlefield.

name: Tendrils of Corruption
text: Tendrils of Corruption deals X damage to target creature and you gain X life, where X is the number of Swamps you control.
flavor: Darkness doesn't always send its minions to do its dirty work.

name: Living Death
text: Each player exiles all creature cards from his or her graveyard, then sacrifices all creatures he or she controls, then puts all cards he or she exiled this way onto the battlefield.

name: Urza's Rage
text: Kicker {8}{R} (You may pay an additional {8}{R} as you cast this spell.)\nUrza's Rage can't be countered by spells or abilities.\nUrza's Rage deals 3 damage to target creature or player. If Urza's Rage was kicked, instead it deals 10 damage to that creature or player and the damage can't be prevented.

name: Thornscape Apprentice
text: {R}, {T}: Target creature gains first strike until end of turn.\n{W}, {T}: Tap target creature.

name: Nomadic Elf
text: {1}{G}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.
flavor: "I've journeyed across Dominaria. Phyrexians are everywhere. Plague is everywhere. There's no place left to hide."

name: Quirion Elves
text: As Quirion Elves enters the battlefield, choose a color.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\n{T}: Add one mana of the chosen color to your mana pool.

name: Sunscape Battlemage
text: Kicker {1}{G} and/or {2}{U} (You may pay an additional {1}{G} and/or {2}{U} as you cast this spell.)\nWhen Sunscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {1}{G} kicker, destroy target creature with flying.\nWhen Sunscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {2}{U} kicker, draw two cards.

name: Thunderscape Battlemage
text: Kicker {1}{B} and/or {G} (You may pay an additional {1}{B} and/or {G} as you cast this spell.)\nWhen Thunderscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {1}{B} kicker, target player discards two cards.\nWhen Thunderscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {G} kicker, destroy target enchantment.

name: Thornscape Battlemage
text: Kicker {R} and/or {W} (You may pay an additional {R} and/or {W} as you cast this spell.)\nWhen Thornscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {R} kicker, it deals 2 damage to target creature or player.\nWhen Thornscape Battlemage enters the battlefield, if it was kicked with its {W} kicker, destroy target artifact.

name: Verduran Emissary
text: Kicker {1}{R} (You may pay an additional {1}{R} as you cast this spell.)\nWhen Verduran Emissary enters the battlefield, if it was kicked, destroy target artifact. It can't be regenerated.

name: Yavimaya Elder
text: When Yavimaya Elder dies, you may search your library for up to two basic land cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.\n{2}, Sacrifice Yavimaya Elder: Draw a card.

name: Charging Troll
text: Vigilance\n{G}: Regenerate Charging Troll.
flavor: They stop for nothing, not even the end of a battle.

name: Gerrard Capashen
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you gain 1 life for each card in target opponent's hand.\n{3}{W}: Tap target creature. Activate this ability only if Gerrard Capashen is attacking.

name: Darigaaz, the Igniter
text: Flying\nWhenever Darigaaz, the Igniter deals combat damage to a player, you may pay {2}{R}. If you do, choose a color, then that player reveals his or her hand and Darigaaz deals damage to the player equal to the number of cards of that color revealed this way.

name: Rith, the Awakener
text: Flying\nWhenever Rith, the Awakener deals combat damage to a player, you may pay {2}{G}. If you do, choose a color, then put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield for each permanent of that color.

name: Treva, the Renewer
text: Flying\nWhenever Treva, the Renewer deals combat damage to a player, you may pay {2}{W}. If you do, choose a color, then you gain 1 life for each permanent of that color.

name: Evasive Action
text: Domain — Counter target spell unless its controller pays {1} for each basic land type among lands you control.
flavor: Effective use of terrain is a lesson good commanders learn quickly.

name: Tribal Flames
text: Domain — Tribal Flames deals X damage to target creature or player, where X is the number of basic land types among lands you control.
flavor: "Fire is the universal language."\n—Jhoira, master artificer

name: Fertile Ground
text: Enchant land\nWhenever enchanted land is tapped for mana, its controller adds one mana of any color to his or her mana pool (in addition to the mana the land produces).
flavor: As Phyrexians descended, Multani paused to reflect on the beauty that might never be seen again.

name: Gerrard's Command
text: Untap target creature. It gets +3/+3 until end of turn.
flavor: "Unless you like the idea of becoming some goblin's lunch, get up and move!"

name: Coalition Relic
text: {T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.\n{T}: Put a charge counter on Coalition Relic.\nAt the beginning of your precombat main phase, remove all charge counters from Coalition Relic. Add one mana of any color to your mana pool for each charge counter removed this way.

name: Narrow Escape
text: Return target permanent you control to its owner's hand. You gain 4 life.
flavor: He could find no strength left to budge, no power left to fight, no will left to live. Luckily, they could find him.

name: Exotic Curse
text: Enchant creature\nDomain — Enchanted creature gets -1/-1 for each basic land type among lands you control.
flavor: Fouler than a necromancer's kiss.\n—Jamuraan expression

name: Harrow
text: As an additional cost to cast Harrow, sacrifice a land.\nSearch your library for up to two basic land cards and put them onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: No spot in nature is truly barren.

name: Armadillo Cloak
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2 and has trample.\nWhenever enchanted creature deals damage, you gain that much life.
flavor: "Don't laugh. It works."

name: Darigaaz's Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
• Darigaaz's Charm deals 3 damage to target creature or player.
• Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Rith's Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Destroy target nonbasic land.
• Put three 1/1 green Saproling creature tokens onto the battlefield.
• Prevent all damage a source of your choice would deal this turn.

name: Treva's Charm
text:
Choose one —
• Destroy target enchantment.
• Exile target attacking creature.
• Draw a card, then discard a card.

name: Power Armor
text: Domain — {3}, {T}: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn for each basic land type among lands you control.
flavor: "Great peril demands formidable weaponry."\n—Urza

name: Allied Strategies
text: Domain — Target player draws a card for each basic land type among lands he or she controls.
flavor: Each commander looked at the others and wondered who would be first to break the alliance.

name: Elfhame Palace
text: Elfhame Palace enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {G} or {W} to your mana pool.
flavor: Llanowar has seven elfhames, or kingdoms, each with its own ruler. Their palaces are objects of awe, wonder, and envy.

name: Shivan Oasis
text: Shivan Oasis enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {R} or {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Only the hardiest explorers survive to eat the fruit.

name: Terramorphic Expanse
text: {T}, Sacrifice Terramorphic Expanse: Search your library for a basic land card and put it onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.

name: Hornet
text: Flying, haste
